<span id="freeTextContainer10754937138860816149">Janet Clay, a journalist, is found floating in the local gym&apos;s pool. Local police classify it as a case of drug over-dose ... but was it?<br/><br/>Aurora Stellar, someone who vaguely knew the journalist, suspects that there&apos;s more to the story than what&apos;s being said. Her own investigation leads to more deaths. This little town seems to be rooted in secrets, lies, and just plain evil.<br/><br/>The more she discovers, the more questions she has. And when her friend&apos;s apartment is a target for arson and when a car hea</span>
  <span id="freeText10754937138860816149" style="display:none">Janet Clay, a journalist, is found floating in the local gym's pool. Local police classify it as a case of drug over-dose ... but was it?<br /><br />Aurora Stellar, someone who vaguely knew the journalist, suspects that there's more to the story than what's being said. Her own investigation leads to more deaths. This little town seems to be rooted in secrets, lies, and just plain evil.<br /><br />The more she discovers, the more questions she has. And when her friend's apartment is a target for arson and when a car heads straight on for her, she knows she's getting close to the truth. But what is the truth .. and how many more lives will be lost?<br /><br />A complex plot, suspenseful mystery, and multi-layered characters make this a must-read. it's a fast-paced action-filled page turner. This is the author's well-crafted debut psychological thriller. I can't wait to see what she does next!<br /><br />Many thanks to the author for the digital copy of IF SHADOWS COULD TELL. Read and reviewed voluntarily, opinions expressed here are unbiased and entirely my own.<br /></span>
