    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_4219138849" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4219138849" />
    <a title="Jean" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28831526-jean"><img alt="Jean" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615997422p2/28831526.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4219138849?book_show_action=true">Sep 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jean" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jean" href="/user/show/28831526-jean">Jean</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28831526-jean?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28831526-jean?shelf=read-for-review">read-for-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/28831526-jean?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4219138849" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11620559783281664241"><i>
  <b> Veritas Numquam Perit&apos;. Committed to finding truth, wherever it leads</b>
</i><br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/53919837.If_Shadows_Could_Tell_an_Aurora_Steller_mystery_novel' title='If Shadows Could Tell an Aurora Steller mystery novel by Granthana Sinha' rel='nofollow noopener'>If Shadows Could Tell: an Aurora Steller mystery novel</a> by Granthana Sinha begins with an eerie, ominous prologue. However, it struck me as though the author was trying too hard, as there was so much descriptive language that it seemed almost melodramatic and over-the-top.<br/><br/>As we meet Aurora Steller – what a great name – she’s an interesting character, but I had difficulty figuring out who she was and what she was about initi</span>
  <span id="freeText11620559783281664241" style="display:none"><i>
  <b> Veritas Numquam Perit'. Committed to finding truth, wherever it leads</b>
</i><br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/53919837.If_Shadows_Could_Tell_an_Aurora_Steller_mystery_novel" title="If Shadows Could Tell an Aurora Steller mystery novel by Granthana Sinha" rel="nofollow noopener">If Shadows Could Tell: an Aurora Steller mystery novel</a> by Granthana Sinha begins with an eerie, ominous prologue. However, it struck me as though the author was trying too hard, as there was so much descriptive language that it seemed almost melodramatic and over-the-top.<br /><br />As we meet Aurora Steller – what a great name – she’s an interesting character, but I had difficulty figuring out who she was and what she was about initially. Throughout the book she is consistently intelligent, very quick to trust, caring, persistent, and a people pleaser. I liked her; but her tendency to want to help solve everyone’s problems cannot possibly end well all the time. Can it?<br /><br />She gets involved with two strangers in trying to prove that Janet Clay’s death was not an accident, and she winds up playing amateur sleuth. In the process, she meets an alluring man, Nicholas. I found him confusing as well. <br /><br />Adding to the mix are the brief, intervening chapters depicting an unidentified child, woman, and man. The former appears to be in turmoil and some kind of danger; the latter is portrayed as dangerous, perhaps even evil. This all plays out at the end, but I found it quite unsettling, and I was never comfortable with the plot.<br /><br />As the story continues, I did settle in enough to become curious about what was actually behind Janet’s death and how these other persons figured into the story, but I also did not fully enjoy this either. The plot is complex, but there were too many factors that just had no explanation.<br /><br />I received a PDF copy of this book from the author in return for my honest review. My opinion and thoughts are my own.<br /><br />3 stars</span>
  <a data-text-id="11620559783281664241" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


