    <a title="May 舞" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20015365-may"><img alt="May 舞" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585662381p2/20015365.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4046449415?book_show_action=true">Jun 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="May 舞" class="user" itemprop="url" name="May 舞" href="/user/show/20015365-may">May 舞</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20015365-may?shelf=crime">crime</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4046449415" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12765458011643284719">This definitely was not my cup of tea. <br/><br/>Right from the start the writing style felt too jarring and overly descriptive; I simply couldn&apos;t bring myself to enjoy a novel where every single action, no matter how banal or trivial, is mentioned. Add to that the superficialilty and shallowness that pervaded the text, which prevented me from empathizing with the characters or feeling anything more than utter annoyance with the ridiculous things they thought and did. <br/><br/>I&apos;m desperately trying to rack my bra</span>
  <span id="freeText12765458011643284719" style="display:none">This definitely was not my cup of tea. <br /><br />Right from the start the writing style felt too jarring and overly descriptive; I simply couldn't bring myself to enjoy a novel where every single action, no matter how banal or trivial, is mentioned. Add to that the superficialilty and shallowness that pervaded the text, which prevented me from empathizing with the characters or feeling anything more than utter annoyance with the ridiculous things they thought and did. <br /><br />I'm desperately trying to rack my brain for something positive to say, but I'm coming up with a blank. <br /><br />An unconvincing and contrived love story ✔ <br />A vaguely tragic background ✔<br />Subpar writing ✔<br />Flat and aggravating characters ✔<br />Predictable, pedestrian, and mind-numbingly boring plot <i>twists</i> ✔<br />A vapid "mystery", a one-dimensional villain, and a pathetic heroine ✔<br />A ludicurous and asinine ending ✔<br /><b>
  <i>Referring to suicide as "the easy way out"</i>
</b> ✔✔✔<br /><br />The only "stellar" thing about <i>If Shadows Could Tell</i> was the number of eyerolls and yawns I experienced, believe me, it was staggering. Reading this novel was sadly a complete waste of my time.</span>
