        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4220483088" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16552809095171503971">The body of Janet Clay was found in a local pool. An autopsy showed a drug overdose. Local authorities assumed she took the drugs then accidentally fell into the pool. Aurora Steller didn&apos;t buy that story. She met Janet for the first time just last week. Nothing about the meeting made her think that Janet used any type of drugs. When a stranger asks Aurora to help find out exactly what happened to Janet, she jumps at the chance to find out.<br/><br/>The first half of this story had a slow pace. I liked Au</span>
  <span id="freeText16552809095171503971" style="display:none">The body of Janet Clay was found in a local pool. An autopsy showed a drug overdose. Local authorities assumed she took the drugs then accidentally fell into the pool. Aurora Steller didn't buy that story. She met Janet for the first time just last week. Nothing about the meeting made her think that Janet used any type of drugs. When a stranger asks Aurora to help find out exactly what happened to Janet, she jumps at the chance to find out.<br /><br />The first half of this story had a slow pace. I liked Aurora, but I was never sure why she was driven to solve this crime. Aurora met various people while asking questions about Janet's life. While doing this, she discovers a few more murders and lots of secrets in this small Montana town. My rating: 3 Stars.<br /><br />Thank you to the author for send me a copy of the book for an honest review.</span>
