<div id="review_4064696294" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4064696294" />
    <a title="Hope&#39;S Bookshelf" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf"><img alt="Hope&#39;S Bookshelf" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1624012245p2/136566317.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4064696294?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hope&#39;S Bookshelf" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hope&#39;S Bookshelf" href="/user/show/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf">Hope&#39;S Bookshelf</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=psychological-thriller">psychological-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=great-ending">great-ending</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=arc">arc</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=review-copy">review-copy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=suspense-novel">suspense-novel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=female-protagonist">female-protagonist</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=woman-sleuth">woman-sleuth</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/136566317-hope-s-bookshelf?shelf=plot-twists">plot-twists</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4064696294" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7414470542404920672">A young journalist ends up dead in a local gym pool with no trace of foul play. A skilled swimmer drowned – suspicious? Oh yes!<br/>Aurora Steller - a young web designer with a curious and intuitive mind, knows there are secrets when she gets involved in the mystery.<br/>The more she investigates the more secrets are brought out, more lives are lost, her own life is put in danger.<br/><br/>The story is muti-layered, jumping between timelines, which by the way was a bit difficult for me to grasp in the beginning. I </span>
  <span id="freeText7414470542404920672" style="display:none">A young journalist ends up dead in a local gym pool with no trace of foul play. A skilled swimmer drowned – suspicious? Oh yes!<br />Aurora Steller - a young web designer with a curious and intuitive mind, knows there are secrets when she gets involved in the mystery.<br />The more she investigates the more secrets are brought out, more lives are lost, her own life is put in danger.<br /><br />The story is muti-layered, jumping between timelines, which by the way was a bit difficult for me to grasp in the beginning. I mean the sub-plots narrated by an unnamed woman and girl (Ivee and Vio) don't have a time stamp. But once I started to understand who the characters actually were and their pivotal importance to the plot, I was glad the year wasn't mentioned. That would've ruined the surprise. The switch between the timelines was effortless. Those who've read the book would agree the immense value of the sub-plots and how much those added to the whole story. <br /><br />Aurora is a well-written character. She is brave, strong and shows ample determination. I don't know if this is going to be a series. If it does she will make a wonderful protagonist for more complex mysteries. <br /><br />My favourite though is going to be Ivet. Her journey is full of storms. Her own story could've made a separate book on its own. By the end of this novel, her arc comes to a full circle. It's really sad she wouldn't probably be there in the next book!<br /><br />I liked the world building since the story is set in two fictional towns in Montana. The descriptions reveal quite a detailed picture of the place. A little bonus was the glimpse into the history of the town. It gives me great pleasure when writers include history for their fictional places. It makes it so much more real. I would've loved to know more about 'the Princess' Evelyn Zircon. Maybe, in the next book?! Maybe.<br /><br />This debut thriller has so many twists I was kept on edge. The story is suspenseful, multi-layered with fully dimensional characters. Skilled writing has allowed a symphonic presence of different emotions in this fast-paced thriller. <br /><br />Special mention is the twist at the end. After the big reveal an additional twist was unexpected. How could I never see that one coming????<br />It was so good it me blew me away. Reminds me of famous movies with clever twist-endings which shock the wits out of you! <br /><br />Worth reading? Yes! Absolutely! <br /><br />I would recommend this book and will clearly enjoy more work by the same author!<br /><br />Note- The author had send a digital complimentary copy in exchange for an honest review.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7414470542404920672" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


