<span id="freeTextContainer1540947539376373777"><strong>Few People are what They Seem...</strong><br/><br/>No spoilers. 3 1/2 stars. While seeking solace in a church, Aura Stellar mistakenly crashes a funeral in progress...<br/><br/>During the service Aura crossed paths with a stranger. Later they met again leaving the church...<br/><br/>... the stranger, Nicolas Davenport, wants to help Aura solve the suspicious death of Janet Clay, an expert swimmer who drowned in the pool of a gym...<br/><br/>The eyes of a stranger can be deceiving and few people are what they seem...<br/><br/>This was a whodunit murder m</span>
  <span id="freeText1540947539376373777" style="display:none"><strong>Few People are what They Seem...</strong><br /><br />No spoilers. 3 1/2 stars. While seeking solace in a church, Aura Stellar mistakenly crashes a funeral in progress...<br /><br />During the service Aura crossed paths with a stranger. Later they met again leaving the church...<br /><br />... the stranger, Nicolas Davenport, wants to help Aura solve the suspicious death of Janet Clay, an expert swimmer who drowned in the pool of a gym...<br /><br />The eyes of a stranger can be deceiving and few people are what they seem...<br /><br />This was a whodunit murder mystery and before you know it many more bodies pile up. This story has a little of everything in it including a twist at the end and it was a good effort for a first novel.<br /><br />This would be a good little Agatha Christie style novel with the help of a good editor and proofer. It also suffered a little due to the many people introduced into the story but overall, if you're looking for a whodunit mystery, this story has it all.</span>
