<span id="freeTextContainer9168436830789087345">This book is full of twists. It has a lot going on with multiple murders, secrets, lies, people living dual lives.<br/><br/>Additional kudos to the author for introducing a parallel narrative that describes events which happened even before the timeline of the actual story. If you are mindful of the information shared in those parallel segments (at the end of each chapter) you can actually figure out the murderer. But still I doubt it. The hints are too subtle and cleverly concealed.<br/>The entire story is fu</span>
  <span id="freeText9168436830789087345" style="display:none">This book is full of twists. It has a lot going on with multiple murders, secrets, lies, people living dual lives.<br /><br />Additional kudos to the author for introducing a parallel narrative that describes events which happened even before the timeline of the actual story. If you are mindful of the information shared in those parallel segments (at the end of each chapter) you can actually figure out the murderer. But still I doubt it. The hints are too subtle and cleverly concealed.<br />The entire story is full of suspense. I kept changing my guess of who could be the actual killer. But I was completely blown away by the ending. It was so innovative and unpredictable. I never saw that one coming.<br />I was glued to the book till the end. I hope there's a sequel to this!!</span>
