<div id="review_4175721816" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4175721816" />
    <a title="Luci Anderson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/138982265-luci-anderson"><img alt="Luci Anderson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1628977626p2/138982265.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4175721816?book_show_action=true">Aug 14, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luci Anderson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luci Anderson" href="/user/show/138982265-luci-anderson">Luci Anderson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138982265-luci-anderson?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138982265-luci-anderson?shelf=suspense">suspense</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138982265-luci-anderson?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138982265-luci-anderson?shelf=twist-ending">twist-ending</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138982265-luci-anderson?shelf=shocking-end">shocking-end</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138982265-luci-anderson?shelf=recommended">recommended</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4175721816" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15296658299240166834">Holy cow! This book is yet another example why mysteries and thrillers happen to be my favorite genre! This book is a psychological mystery thriller with lots of twists and interesting characters. Most of the story is told from the perspective of a young web designer named Aurora &apos;Aura&apos; Steller. What appealed to me is how the story is laid out in a multi dimensional way. I loved that this novel incorporated multiple perspectives, following Aurora and two other unnamed characters (who are later r</span>
  <span id="freeText15296658299240166834" style="display:none">Holy cow! This book is yet another example why mysteries and thrillers happen to be my favorite genre! This book is a psychological mystery thriller with lots of twists and interesting characters. Most of the story is told from the perspective of a young web designer named Aurora 'Aura' Steller. What appealed to me is how the story is laid out in a multi dimensional way. I loved that this novel incorporated multiple perspectives, following Aurora and two other unnamed characters (who are later revealed of course). This style of storytelling isn't something I've read before in any other thriller story. I thought it made the whole book stand out from the lot and added further intrigue. The chapters and mini chapters go back and forth between two separate timelines, one set in the present day with the latter set years and months ago. I wasn't quite sure of what to expect from the mini chapters in the beginning. But it turned out to be the actual back story of the main plot. Toward the end of the story it all made sense and everything played out perfectly. I enjoyed the pacing of the novel, specially how the clues were revealed little by little with each chapter. <br />However this book can be really really hard for many readers. This is a pretty serious story with complicated characters, timelines and plot. The storyline is complex if not paid proper attention to. The twist at the end was remarkable to say the least but I'm certain no one will see that coming (trust me on this!) I liked Aurora. She was someone I would love to be friends with in real life. The story doesn't show her as someone who does everything right. She makes mistakes, takes risks, does stupid and reckless things in order save those she loves. She felt very real to me. I loved going through the events through her eyes. This is an addictive and entertaining thriller, a real page-turner for sure. Honestly, it's such a good book it will keep you guessing all the way through. <br />Easy 5 stars from me. I'll keep a look out for the next by Ms. Sinha.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15296658299240166834" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


