<div id="review_4127172792" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4127172792" />
    <a title="Anne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/57161856-anne"><img alt="Anne" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4127172792?book_show_action=true">Aug 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Anne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Anne" href="/user/show/57161856-anne">Anne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4127172792" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9928187076190393922">This was a fascinating twisty novel of suspense! Set in a small Montana town, it chronicles Aurora and her friend Suz&apos;s attempts to figure out why a young woman, Janet Clay suddenly disappears. And when she turns up dead, things get dicey as nothing is as it appears. Lots of characters and red herrings in this one, and also goes back and forth from present to past (with a young girl&apos;s voice that isn&apos;t identified). So there are plenty of mysteries here and they all tie together but your head may </span>
  <span id="freeText9928187076190393922" style="display:none">This was a fascinating twisty novel of suspense! Set in a small Montana town, it chronicles Aurora and her friend Suz's attempts to figure out why a young woman, Janet Clay suddenly disappears. And when she turns up dead, things get dicey as nothing is as it appears. Lots of characters and red herrings in this one, and also goes back and forth from present to past (with a young girl's voice that isn't identified). So there are plenty of mysteries here and they all tie together but your head may be spinning trying to figure it out! So don't try...just get on this roller-coaster ride and enjoy the dips and crazy turns as you will be satisfied at the end!<br />Thanks to the author in exchange for an honest review!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9928187076190393922" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


