<div id="review_4148011032" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4148011032" />
    <a title="Mark Walker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/138400616-mark-walker"><img alt="Mark Walker" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627835241p2/138400616.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4148011032?book_show_action=true">Aug 01, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mark Walker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mark Walker" href="/user/show/138400616-mark-walker">Mark Walker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138400616-mark-walker?shelf=twist-end">twist-end</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138400616-mark-walker?shelf=mystery-thriller">mystery-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138400616-mark-walker?shelf=psychological-thriller">psychological-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/138400616-mark-walker?shelf=recommended">recommended</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4148011032" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10585650957049289896">Twists, twists and more twists. This book has so many unexpected twists and turns that I never thought the &apos;twist-ending&apos; it promotes could&apos;ve surprised me more. It not only surprised me, it blew me away.<br/><br/>The characters are all nicely written. The investigation is carried out by a young web designer named Aurora Steller (not a professional detective). She is a fiercely determined and strong character, with her own personal history of guilt and pain. The timelines were hard to follow in the beginn</span>
  <span id="freeText10585650957049289896" style="display:none">Twists, twists and more twists. This book has so many unexpected twists and turns that I never thought the 'twist-ending' it promotes could've surprised me more. It not only surprised me, it blew me away.<br /><br />The characters are all nicely written. The investigation is carried out by a young web designer named Aurora Steller (not a professional detective). She is a fiercely determined and strong character, with her own personal history of guilt and pain. The timelines were hard to follow in the beginning, but everything fits fabulously in the end.<br /><br />There should be a mention though that this isn't an easy read. Not for readers who expect an easy murder mystery. I found the story mind blowing but it's complicated with a list of characters and layers. Special part is the 'subplot'. That added more meat to the book.<br /><br />Applaudable debut! Looking forward to the next in the series.<br /><br />||Recommended||</span>
  <a data-text-id="10585650957049289896" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


