<div id="review_4376907313" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4376907313" />
    <a title="Liliyana Shadowlyn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/51641311-liliyana-shadowlyn"><img alt="Liliyana Shadowlyn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627098510p2/51641311.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4376907313?book_show_action=true">Dec 07, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Liliyana Shadowlyn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Liliyana Shadowlyn" href="/user/show/51641311-liliyana-shadowlyn">Liliyana Shadowlyn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/51641311-liliyana-shadowlyn?shelf=2021-reads">2021-reads</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4376907313" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12007866039490392241">Once you crack open this book, you won&apos;t want to stop reading. It really speeds up in the second half of the book, although there are plenty of twists to keep you guessing throughout. I loved Aurora - she might not be a professional detective, but she isn&apos;t afraid to dig for the truth when she suspects something is off. Sinha does a great job of bringing the scenes to life, and really draws the reader into the story itself quite easily. If you like murder mysteries where the sleuth isn&apos;t a cop, </span>
  <span id="freeText12007866039490392241" style="display:none">Once you crack open this book, you won't want to stop reading. It really speeds up in the second half of the book, although there are plenty of twists to keep you guessing throughout. I loved Aurora - she might not be a professional detective, but she isn't afraid to dig for the truth when she suspects something is off. Sinha does a great job of bringing the scenes to life, and really draws the reader into the story itself quite easily. If you like murder mysteries where the sleuth isn't a cop, and don't mind a few chills along the way, you're going to love this book!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12007866039490392241" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


