<div id="review_3592190046" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3592190046" />
    <a title="Naveen Iyer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/122801151-naveen-iyer"><img alt="Naveen Iyer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602513590p2/122801151.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3592190046?book_show_action=true">Oct 12, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Naveen Iyer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Naveen Iyer" href="/user/show/122801151-naveen-iyer">Naveen Iyer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3592190046" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15051807156475089890">I thought it was just a regular murder mystery. But...oh no!<br/>This is one of the most exciting psychological thrillers I&apos;ve read in a really really loooooong time. This literally kept me hooked till the very last word.<br/><br/>&quot;Truth. <br/>When you search for the truth, you try every means to unearth the lies, you look into every shadowy corner for answers. But the path you follow, depends on what you believe the truth really is.<br/>When you realize your belief has been misled, when all the answers you collected on</span>
  <span id="freeText15051807156475089890" style="display:none">I thought it was just a regular murder mystery. But...oh no!<br />This is one of the most exciting psychological thrillers I've read in a really really loooooong time. This literally kept me hooked till the very last word.<br /><br />"Truth. <br />When you search for the truth, you try every means to unearth the lies, you look into every shadowy corner for answers. But the path you follow, depends on what you believe the truth really is.<br />When you realize your belief has been misled, when all the answers you collected only hide a greater lie ― that's when the definition of truth changes. That’s when it seems unattainable. That’s when you know you aren't even close."<br /><br />Now that's deep. <br /><br />The story has quite a lot of characters and you'll end up suspecting everybody. (At least I did. But I still got it wrong!😕). I loved the explaining part in the end and the conclusion given to each character.<br /><br />From page one it's suspenseful, fast paced, and full of twists. But the end twist beats the lot! It's outstanding.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15051807156475089890" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


